FIN-004 — Banking Stress

Rule Information

Rule ID: FIN-004
Domain: Financial Resilience
Category: Banking System Stability
Status: Active
Version: 1.0
Repository: Sextant Rule Library

Purpose

Evaluate the resilience of the banking sector during periods of financial stress and assess potential cascading effects across interconnected systems.

Scenario

Banks experience increasing financial pressure due to deteriorating asset quality, funding constraints, declining confidence, or heightened market volatility.

The scenario evaluates:

- Banking sector stability
- Capital adequacy
- Funding availability
- Deposit stability
- Credit market conditions

Primary Indicators

- Capital Adequacy Ratio (CAR)
- Non-Performing Loan (NPL) ratio
- Loan-to-Deposit Ratio (LDR)
- Deposit withdrawal trends
- Interbank lending activity
- Bank funding spreads
- Credit default indicators

Risk Levels

GREEN

Normal banking system conditions.

Banks remain well-capitalised with stable funding and adequate liquidity.

No contingency actions required.

YELLOW

Early signs of banking sector stress.

Monitor:

- Capital adequacy
- Liquidity levels
- Deposit movements
- Credit quality

Action:

Increase supervisory monitoring and review institutional resilience.

ORANGE

Significant banking sector stress.

Indicators:

- Rising non-performing loans
- Reduced liquidity
- Funding pressures
- Declining market confidence

Potential Cascade:

Banking Stress
↓
Credit Tightening
↓
Reduced Lending
↓
Economic Slowdown

Action:

Prepare contingency measures and strengthen financial stability monitoring.

RED

Severe banking system instability.

Indicators:

- Critical liquidity shortages
- Rapid deposit withdrawals
- Capital deterioration
- Widespread financial instability

Potential Cascade:

Banking Crisis
↓
Financial Market Disruption
↓
Economic Contraction
↓
Cross-Domain Systemic Risk

Action:

Activate emergency financial stability procedures and coordinate institutional response.

Cross-Domain Dependencies

Financial (FIN)
↓
Infrastructure (INF)
↓
Cyber (CYB)
↓
Data Centre Operations (DC)

Stress within the banking sector may propagate operational and systemic risks across interconnected domains.

Contingency Actions

- Monitor banking system indicators continuously
- Assess capital and liquidity positions
- Review funding resilience
- Evaluate systemic contagion risks
- Increase reporting frequency
- Escalate to institutional risk management when thresholds are exceeded

Simulation Output

- Risk Level
- Cascade Path
- Affected Domains
- Recommended Contingency Actions
- Audit Log Entry

